      "content": "Research consistently shows that generous social safety nets have a negative effect on labor participation, as high benefits reduce the incentive to work. Studies indicate that when the replacement rate for unemployment or disability benefits is too high, it creates a \"benefits trap\" where individuals prefer staying on welfare to avoid losing their income. Therefore, the expansion of these programs has indeed been a major factor in the decline of labor participation rates over the last decade.",
